 position as a tutor the information session for the drop in tutor positions is friday feb 10 from 3 4pm in the hume writing center application process rwt positions applications were due via resjobs at noon on tuesday january 17 letters of recommendation posted also through resjobs were due january 23 at noon interview will be held the week of feb 6 drop in tutor positions applications are due february 15 5 00 pm via cardinal careers search for undergraduate writing tutor if you have applied to become an rwt you do not need to apply to cardinal careers if you also wish to be considered for a dro p in tutor position you ll be asked to submit a 500 word essay on why you want to be a tutor see details on cdc website a two paragraph sample of academic writing an unofficial transcript these three items should be together in one pdf in addition you ll be asked to bring a letter of recommendation from a faculty member who knows your writing to the interview if you wish to talk about the positions or the application process please contact julia bleakney or the peer tutor coordinators hwc programs writing in the major introductory seminars honors writing and boot camp digital media consulting pwr stanford university 590 escondido mall stanford ca 94305 3069 650 723 2631 contact us terms of use copyright complaints site by wired moon
